    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I see. So, if we follow that logic, it sounds like any form of content moderation by the state is essentially just censorship. Do you think there's any legitimate way for a government to regulate the internet without violating those principles, or is the whole concept of 'regulating the digital space' fundamentally incompatible with free speech?",
